  "//overrides-audit-notes": [
    "serialize-javascript: HIGH (GHSA RCE via RegExp.flags) — forced to ^7.0.0 via override; only affects @wdio/mocha-framework (devDep test runner, not production wallet code). Fixed 2026-07-05.",
    "elliptic: LOW — forced to ^6.6.1; mitigates transitive ECDSA risky-primitive advisory across WalletConnect/Ledger/Trezor sub-trees.",
    "@stablelib/ed25519 (WalletConnect moderate chain): no upstream fix without regressive downgrade of web3wallet (1.16.1→1.13.0). Acknowledged 2026-07-05. Wallet key signing uses @noble/curves — unaffected. Revisit when @walletconnect/relay-auth ships a patched 1.x release.",
    "protobufjs: MODERATE (GHSA-j3f2-48v5-ccww DoS via infinite loop in .proto option parsing) — bumped ^7.6.4→^7.6.5 (patched). Reaches production tree via @trezor/connect-web hardware-wallet transport; also clears the @trezor/{connect,connect-web,protobuf,transport} moderate chain. Off the signing path (@noble/@scure). Fixed 2026-07-21.",
    "appium-uiautomator2-driver chain (HIGH: shell-quote GHSA-395f-4hp3-45gv, plus @appium/{support,base-driver,docutils}, appium-{adb,android-driver,chromedriver,uiautomator2-driver}; LOW: body-parser GHSA-v422-hmwv-36x6): ACCEPTED dev-tree residual 2026-07-21. All DoS-only, entirely inside the appium-uiautomator2-driver devDependency (Android E2E test harness) — never imported by src/, never bundled in the production wallet. @appium/support@7.2.5 pins shell-quote at an exact 1.8.4 and a sibling teen_process edge lets npm dedupe onto it, so a shell-quote/body-parser override is silently ignored (verified). npm's only working fix is a 7-major-version downgrade of the driver (8.1.0->1.75.0) that would break the E2E suite. Revisit when appium-uiautomator2-driver ships a release whose @appium/support depends on a patched shell-quote (>1.8.4). Re-verified via upstream watcher 2026-07-21: @appium/support still 7.2.5 (still pins shell-quote 1.8.4), appium-uiautomator2-driver still 8.1.0 — residual unchanged, still blocked."
  ],
